

Rootin Tootin is a fast RESTful web server and framework written in D. It is 
designed to scale well by default, while still providing a developer experience 
similar to Ruby on Rails.

1. Add the repository for the ldc compiler and tango libraries
# ubuntu
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:d-language-packagers

#fedora
# or follow the instructions here:
http://www.dsource.org/projects/ldc/


2. Install the dependencies for your distro:
# ubuntu
sudo apt-get install mysql-client mysql-server libmysqlclient15-dev \
python-mysqldb python-pexpect python-mako build-essential \
bzr ldc libtango-ldc-dev

# fedora
sudo yum groupinstall "Development Tools"
sudo yum install mysql mysql-server MySQL-python pexpect python-mako bzr ldc


3. Move to your install location, download the code, add path to bashrc:
cd ~
bzr branch lp:rester rootintootin
cd rootintootin
sudo make install


4. Copy the examples to your desktop, to play with:
cp -r examples/ ~/Desktop/examples/
cd ~/Desktop/examples/users


5. Change the site's database user and port:
./gen configure database user:root password:password
./gen configure server port:3000


6. Generate, build, run:
./gen create database
./gen migrate
./build
./run


7. In your web browser navigate to http://localhost:3000/users and you should 
see a basic CRUD example.


8. Now look at the code and start hacking. I will add more formal documentation 
when things are a little more fleshed out.


